main event: A white object emitting light from the rear was sighted near Winslow, Arizona on September 21, 1954.
interesting points: The object was visible for approximately 30 seconds before disappearing to the east.
Another airline flight over St. George, Utah reported sighting the same object heading approximately 152 degrees from their location.
The report concludes that there is insufficient data for evaluation.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of approximately 20,000 feet and north of Green Airway Number Four.
The report mentions that an additional follow-up was expected.
sighted object: a white object emitting light from the rear
